instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "Architecture follows ISO 23247 Reference Architecture. Functional Elements (FEs) are mapped onto ROS 2 packages, each containing one or more ROS 2 nodes that implement the twin logic. The system is distributed across three logical entities: 1) Physical Twin Entity (hosted on on‑board vehicle hardware, managing raw sensor data, point‑cloud clustering, actuation); 2) Digital Twin Entity (hosted on edge/edge core, responsible for data processing, state estimation, control algorithms, data storage); 3) User Entity (providing a User Interface FE split into 3D Visualization and Control Panel). Each FE communicates via ROS 2 DDS middleware, providing publish‑subscribe message passing, whereas point‑cloud clustering may be implemented using PCL and tracking with OpenCV. Resource management is achieved by deploying each FE to specific compute nodes, enabling realistic scaling and fault isolation. The absence of a dedicated FE for the Data Storage component illustrates the flexible mapping approach permitted by ISO 23247."
]

