    base:desc "The Digital Twin system complies with ISO 23247 – Digital twin framework for manufacturing, specifically Part 2 – Reference Architecture. This standard prescribes an entity‑based framework that groups functionality into four main entities: the Observable Manufacturing Element (OME) representing the physical asset; the Data Collection and Device Control Entity, which gathers data from and issues control commands to the OME; the Digital Twin Entity, which provides the digital representation of the OME; and the User Entity, which offers user interfaces for monitoring and interacting with the Digital Twin. Each of these entities is further decomposed into functional entities (FEs) responsible for tasks such as data transformation, actuating the OME, providing human‑interpretable formats, or interfacing with the user. ISO 23247 does not mandate specific implementation mechanisms; however, the document cites OPC Unified Architecture as a potential protocol for integration. The system’s architecture, as described, follows the ISO 23247 reference architecture, ensuring that the DT can interoperate within the broader industrial digital twin ecosystem and adhere to the prescribed standards for manufacturing digital twins."
]
